                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Great Britain/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-15T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 15—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>294. Yesterday in the House of Commons replying to Asquith, the Chancellor of the
                    Exchequer quoted the British indebtedness <pb facs="0524" n="404"
                        xml:id="pg_404"/> to the United States at present rate of exchange as
                    approximately £938,000,000. He stated: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Our relation to the United States in the matter of the debt which we owe
                            to that great country is engaging our attention at the present moment. I
                            welcome and reciprocate the views which were expressed by the right
                            honorable gentleman, the member for Paisley, that our debt to the United
                            States of America is one of solemn obligation which undoubtedly we shall
                            meet. There is no question about that and the request which the United
                            States has made to us recently to consider the question of funding the
                            debt and placing it upon a suitable and equitable foundation is one
                            which will be completely met. There is no question of the attitude of
                            the country on the matter.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
